    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Handmade paper that is produced in a centuries-old traditional manner in Japan from the fiber of gampi tree bark, kozo (mulberry), the mitsumata shrub, bamboo, hemp, rice, or wheat.</Note_Text>
